Sentencas: The presented study focuses on a numerical simulation of the transport phenomena inside a solid oxide fuel cell anode.
Titulo: The prediction of the polarization curves of a solid oxide fuel cell anode with an artificial neural network supported numerical simulation

Sentencas: The classical mathematical model leads to a notable discrepancy between measured and predicted overpotentials.
Titulo: The prediction of the polarization curves of a solid oxide fuel cell anode with an artificial neural network supported numerical simulation

Sentencas: One of the possible reasons is the assumption of the constant values of electrochemical reaction charge transfer coefficients.
Titulo: The prediction of the polarization curves of a solid oxide fuel cell anode with an artificial neural network supported numerical simulation

Sentencas: A modified formulation of the problem includes data-driven correction of reaction charge transfer coefficients in the electrochemical reaction model.
Titulo: The prediction of the polarization curves of a solid oxide fuel cell anode with an artificial neural network supported numerical simulation

Sentencas: Here we show a dedicated computational scheme in which an artificial neural network updates the charge transfer coefficients depending on the operational conditions and the available datasets.
Titulo: The prediction of the polarization curves of a solid oxide fuel cell anode with an artificial neural network supported numerical simulation

Sentencas: The neural network was trained on twelve experimental data points of an anode's polarization curve obtained from the literature.
Titulo: The prediction of the polarization curves of a solid oxide fuel cell anode with an artificial neural network supported numerical simulation

Sentencas: The training set contained data for the anode operating in two different temperatures - 800 degrees C and 900 degrees C.
Titulo: The prediction of the polarization curves of a solid oxide fuel cell anode with an artificial neural network supported numerical simulation

Sentencas: The test set contained additional six data points for an anode operating at 1000 degrees C. Charge transfer coefficients were proposed by the Artificial Neural Network as a functional relation of the temperature and withdrawn current.
Titulo: The prediction of the polarization curves of a solid oxide fuel cell anode with an artificial neural network supported numerical simulation

Sentencas: The results of the predictions are juxtaposed with the experimental data from the literature.
Titulo: The prediction of the polarization curves of a solid oxide fuel cell anode with an artificial neural network supported numerical simulation

Sentencas: It was shown that an Artificial Neural Network could improve an electrochemical reaction model in Solid Oxide Fuel Cell modeling.
Titulo: The prediction of the polarization curves of a solid oxide fuel cell anode with an artificial neural network supported numerical simulation
